<div id="aueditable"><!--DO NOT MODIFY THIS LINE AND ABOVE-->

<h1>Galileo Galilei</h1><div id="pubinfo"><em>First published Fri Mar 4, 2005; substantive revision Wed Dec 17, 2025</em></div>

<div id="preamble">

<p>
Galileo Galilei (1564&ndash;1642) plays a central role in any history
of science and many histories of philosophy. He is a&mdash;if not
<em>the</em>&mdash;central figure of the Scientific Revolution of the
seventeenth century. By middle age, his achievements in physics and
astronomy, his support for the Copernican theory of the solar system,
and his later condemnation by the Roman Church elevated him to heroic
status even during his lifetime. His story has been continuously
retold for more than 400 years. This article summarizes his
contributions, focusing on some of the issues that have garnered
attention from philosophers.</p>
</div> 

<div id="toc">

<!--Entry Contents-->
<ul>
	<li><a href="#Intro">1. Introduction</a></li>
	<li><a href="#BriefBio">2. Brief Biography</a></li>
