pp. 99&ndash;113.</li>

<li>Machamer, Peter, and Andrea Woody, 1994, &ldquo;A Model of
Intelligibility in Science: Using Galileo&rsquo;s Balance as a Model
for Understanding the Motion of Bodies,&rdquo; <em>Science and
Education</em>, 3 (3): 215&ndash;244.</li>

<li>Mancosu, Paolo, 1996, <em>Philosophy of Mathematics and
Mathematical Practice in the Seventeenth Century</em>. New York:
Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Mayer, Thomas F. (ed.), 2012, <em>The Trial of Galileo
1612&ndash;1633</em>, North York, Ontario: University of Toronto
Press.</li>

<li>McMullin, Ernan (ed.), 1967, <em>Galileo, Man of Science</em>, New
York: Basic Books.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1998, &ldquo;Galileo on Science and
Scripture,&rdquo; in P. Machamer (ed.), <em>Cambridge Companion to
